The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, December 26, 2003 				 Samsung to launch biggest flat TV
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Dec. 25: Samsung India Electronics, the consumer electronics giant, is all set to introduce the biggest flat panel colour television range with new models of plasma, LCD, LCD projection and 100 hertz flat CTVs in the new year.																								We are seeking to develop the market for flat panel TVs in India and expect to take an early lead in this product segment owing to the technological edge that we enjoy with our DNIe technology, said Ravinder Zutshi, director-sales, Samsung India.																								DNIe is a technological breakthrough from Samsung. It comprises a set of advanced image processing technologies that ensure enhanced contrast, detail white tone and noise reduction for visual displays such as plasma and LCD projection televisions.																								The company will also be doubling the number of DigitAllhomes next year. The consumer electronics giant inaugurated its 21st DigitAllhome at Noida, near Delhi earlier this week. 																								Samsung DigitAllhome represents a new concept of display introduced wherein the companys complete range of advanced, high quality products are displayed in a more interactive manner with a more lifestyle orientation to the display.																								The customer can actually visualise the products in his / her own home settings. Thus, our efforts in creating a modern kitchen or a home-theatre experience in a living room set up using Samsung LCD projection TV and DVD player comes through, said Zutshi.																								According to him, the company expects the flat TV contribution to grow from 22 per cent at present to over 35 per cent level next year.																								In another development, SIE is setting up a $1.5-million institute to train its service engineers. The institute will begin operations in the first quarter of 2004. This centre is a part of Samsungs strategic focus on after-sales service network and customer satisfaction. 
